      <p>On the other hand, we could not accept this priority as the general tendency among peak callers, because the majority (namely, 81.8%) of datasets had other priorities. To obtain more reliable inference, we considered the relaxed arrangements for comparison of pairs of peak callers. In this case the most frequent priority among 12 distinct ones was
